//Check whether a tree is binary or not

class Solution {
    boolean isBST(Node root) {
        return isBSTUtil(root, Long.MIN_VALUE, Long.MAX_VALUE);
    }

    boolean isBSTUtil(Node node, long min, long max) {
        if (node == null) return true;

        if (node.data <= min || node.data >= max) return false;

        return isBSTUtil(node.left, min, node.data) &&
               isBSTUtil(node.right, node.data, max);
    }
}

Given the root of a binary tree. Your task is to return the left view of the binary tree. 
The left view of a binary tree is the set of nodes visible when the tree is viewed from the left side.

Note: If the tree is empty, return an empty list.

nodes = [1, 2, 3, N, N, 4, N, N, 5, N, N]
Output: [1, 2, 4, 5]
